EM flows: Global- mandated EMDD funds saw inflows worth US\(60m last week versus inflows worth US\)1.6bn in the previous week.

Hard currency global- mandated funds saw inflows of US\(208m, from inflows of US\)925m in the prior week. Regional/country funds saw US\(14m in inflows from US\)230m in inflows in the prior week. This left hard currency funds recording inflows of US\(222m, compared with inflows of US\)1.2bn in the prior week. Sovereign funds saw inflows of US\(146m, from inflows of US\)315m last week. Mixed funds saw inflows of US\(97m, while corporate funds saw outflows of US\)21m. ETFs saw inflows of US\(79m, from inflows of US\)187m last week, while non- ETFs saw inflows of US\)144m, from inflows of US\)969m a week ago.

Local currency global- mandated funds saw inflows of US\(375m, from inflows of US\)298m in the prior week, leaving overall local currency fund inflows strong again at US\)526m, from inflows of US\)1.8bn the previous week. Regional/country inflows rose, seeing US\)151m in inflows, from US \(1.5bn in inflows last week, with Asia registering US\)4m in outflows. ETF inflows improved to US\)438m, from US\)1.5bn in inflows in the prior week. Non- ETFs also saw improvements, with inflows of US\)87m, from inflows of US\)301m a week ago.

Overall, EMDD funds saw inflows worth US\)844m last week versus inflows worth US\)3.2bn in the previous week. Year- to- date returns stand at 8.7% and 14.2% for hard currency and local currency, respectively.
EM credit issuance: There was US\(11.4bn in issuance this week, versus US\)6.1bn the previous week.

There was nEM sovereign issuance this week, keeping YTD sovereign issuance at US\)166.7bn, at historical highs, including above this point in 2020 by US\)3.6bn, and up US\)21.9bn versus this point in 2024. Sovereign issuance is 73% of the way through our full- year issuance expectation. Potential issuers through September include Indonesia, Kuwait, Latvia, Panama, Philippines, Poland and Romania in the IG space, and Bahrain, Brazil, Colombia, Oman, Sharjah, South Africa, Egypt, Kenya, Cameroon and Turkey in the HY space. For sources, see EM sovereign issuance sources.
ESG issuance: There was US\(4.3bn in ESG- labelled bond issuance in EM last week, bringing year- to- date ESG issuance to US\)71.2bn.
For ESG funds, hard currency funds saw inflows of US\(8m, local currency funds registered inflows of US\)84m and blended currency funds

Overweight (O or Over) - The stock's total return is expected to exceed the total return of the relevant country MSCI Index or the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis over the next 12-18 months.

Equal-weight (E or Equal) - The stock's total return is expected to be in line with the total return of the relevant country MSCI Index or the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis over the next 12-18 months.

Not-Rated (NR) - Currently the analyst does not have adequate conviction about the stock's total return relative to the relevant country MSCI Index or the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.

Underweight (U or Under) - The stock's total return is expected to be below the total return of the relevant country MSCI Index or the average total return of the analyst's industry (or industry team's) coverage universe, on a risk-adjusted basis, over the next 12-18 months.
